modules.description: Provides operations to manage and manipulate a string buffer with position tracking, including advancing the position, extracting substrings, and checking content. Works with a custom type representing a string and an offset, enabling efficient traversal and inspection. Used to process input incrementally, such as parsing tokens or extracting segments without copying data.

Parses input streams using a set of combinators that chain and transform parsing logic. Works with character streams and custom token types to build recursive descent parsers. Enables parsing of structured text formats like CSV, simple DSLs, and custom data encodings.

Tracks a string and an offset, allowing efficient traversal and extraction of substrings. Supports advancing the position and inspecting content without data duplication. Processes input incrementally, such as parsing tokens or slicing segments. Operates on a custom type combining a string and an integer offset.
